\par
\pard\sa120\b 10.2 Historical Validation Example\b0\par
\pard For March 2022 historical ranking (actual data), top jurisdictions include:\par
\pard 1. Chadayamangalam\par
\pard 2. Kottarakkara\par
\pard 3. Venjarammood\par
\par
\pard\sa120\b 10.3 Forecast Interpretation\b0\par
\pard Predicted rankings may not match a single historical snapshot because forecast reflects multi-year patterns and learned trend behavior. High-volume jurisdictions can remain top across multiple forecast months.\par
\par
\pard ---\par
\par
\pard\qc\sa180\b\fs28 11. CIVIL ENGINEERING INTERPRETATION\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard The platform supports practical planning decisions:\par
\pard 1. **Persistent hotspot detection** for corridor prioritization.\par
\pard 2. **Temporal pattern analysis** (month/day/night) for enforcement scheduling.\par
\pard 3. **Severity-risk interpretation** under different geometry and junction contexts.\par
\pard 4. **Infrastructure intervention planning**:\par
\pard    - shoulder and median treatment\par
\pard    - junction redesign\par
\pard    - night-visibility improvement\par
\pard    - signage and speed management\par
\par
\pard ---\par
\par
\pard\qc\sa180\b\fs28 12. VALIDATION, RELIABILITY, AND ERROR ANALYSIS\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard\sa120\b 12.1 Data Reliability\b0\par
\pard Input inconsistencies are reduced by deterministic preprocessing rules and fallback reconstruction logic.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\b 12.2 Model Reliability\b0\par
\pard Cross-validation and hold-out evaluation used for severity model comparison.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\b 12.3 Forecast Reliability Notes\b0\par
\pard 1. Forecast is univariate-plus-seasonality and trend-based.\par
\pard 2. External factors are not yet included; interpret as planning guidance, not deterministic truth.\par
\par
\pard ---\par
\par
\pard\qc\sa180\b\fs28 13. LIMITATIONS\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard 1. No explicit traffic exposure variables (AADT/volume).\par
\pard 2. No weather/rainfall/external event covariates.\par
\pard 3. No uncertainty bands shown for forecast output.\par
\pard 4. Jurisdiction-level aggregation may hide micro blackspots.\par
\par
\pard ---\par
\par
\pard\qc\sa180\b\fs28 14. CONCLUSION\b0\fs22\par
